In this article, White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest discusses various topics during a press gaggle aboard Air Force One. He mentions that President Obama will be delivering a commencement address at The Ohio State University, where he will challenge graduates to use their education to be engaged citizens in American democracy. Earnest also comments on the escalating conflict in Syria, the recent deaths of American troops in Afghanistan, and the Israeli government's concerns about Hezbollah obtaining advanced weapons. He emphasizes the close coordination between the United States and Israel on national security issues. Earnest briefly touches on the administration's efforts to pass comprehensive immigration reform and the ongoing push for common-sense gun control measures.